cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.MM

This paper deals with interference prediction in mobile ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to network communication and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes a general-order linear model for node mobility, which involves mathematical analysis and modeling, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in dealing with complex mobilities, which can be related to control systems and system dynamics, leading to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible category. Furthermore, the paper uses a compound Gaussian point process functional to obtain analytical results, which involves probability theory and stochastic processes, making cs.MA (Machine Learning) another possible category. Finally, the paper also discusses simulation results, which can be related to multimedia and computer graphics, leading to cs.MM (Multimedia) as another possible category.
